<h1 class="mainbody_header_w">Cheat Happens Privacy Policy and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</h1>
<div class="mainbody_wide"><p>This page outlines how Cheat Happens (https://www.cheathappens.com) complies with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) as well as its Privacy Policies. Cheat Happens is classified as a "data controller" under the GDPR. If you have any questions regarding this information, please contact Chris O'Rorke (see: <a href="aboutus.asp">About Us</a>).</p>
<p>LAST REVISION: DEC 28, 2018
<p class="header16 openbold"><u>CHEAT HAPPENS WEBSITE</u>:</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Personal Information Collection and Use</p>
<p>Cheat Happens is the sole owner of the information collected on this site. We will not sell, share, or rent this information to others in ways different from what is disclosed in this statement. Cheat Happens collects information from our users at several different points on our website. Third parties that advertise through our website may also collect information through cookies and you may find their privacy policy at the corresponding advertiser's website. Our primary advertiser is Yieldlove and you can find their privacy policy here: <a href="yieldlove.asp">https://www.cheathappens.com/yieldlove.asp</a>. Users may opt-out of the cookies and data being collected by all third parties at any time (see bottom of page).</p>
<p>Cheat Happens offers memberships which include both free and paid levels. We only require and store User Alias, E-Mail Address, Password, Security Question and Answer and IP address(es). We do not ask for or store other personally identifiable information such as Real Name, Date of Birth, Social Security Number or any kind of Financial Data. All financial data is processed securely via either PayPal (<a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/webapps/mpp/ua/privacy-full">PayPal Privacy Policy</a>) or Authorize.net (<a href="https://www.authorize.net/company/privacy/">Authorize.net Privacy Policy</a>).
<p class="header16 openbold">Site Security</p>
<p>Cheat Happens operates only using SSL for all pages served through our site. All data is stored securely behind 3 independent firewalls in an effort to secure all data, personal or otherwise. Cheat Happens utilizes services by Cloudflare to help increase security, improve the performance of our our site and protect against DDoS and other attacks. Under the GDPR, Cloudflare acts as a "data processor" and we have a signed Data Processing Addendum (DPA) on file. You can view Cloudflare's privacy policy here: <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/security-policy/">https://www.cloudflare.com/security-policy/</a>.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Third Party Advertisers</p>
We work with third-party companies to serve ads when you visit our website. These companies may use information (not including your name, address, email address or telephone number) about your visits to our website in order to provide advertisements on this website, other websites and other forms of media about goods and services that may be of interest to you. If you would like more information about this practice and to know your choices about not having this information used by these companies, please <a href="https://www.networkadvertising.org/consumer/opt_out.asp">click here</a>.
<p class="header16 openbold">Cookies</p>
<p>A cookie is a piece of data stored on the user’s hard drive containing information about the user. Cheat Happens uses cookies to enhance the user's experience, often allowing a user to browse the site more quickly. Some cookies are necessary for the website to function, especially those used when signed in as a registered user. Some of our business partners use cookies on our site (for example, advertisers). Additional cookies may include those used for gathering site statictics and analytics, user preferences and marketing. Under the GDPR, users may opt in or out of all cookies not deemed necessary. All visitors will be prompted to either allow or decline these cookies upon first visiting our site and then may change their previous choices at any time (see bottom of page). </p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Log Files and IPs</p>
<p>IP addressess are logged in the server's log file which is used for administering the site. Log files contain no personally identifiable information. Under very rare circumstances, log files may be furnished to 3rd party advertisers for proof of traffic information. IPs are also stored within our message board area and are used to ban those users that do not comply with our message board rules. IPs are also documented upon user registration, login, when downloading files and during our trainer authentication process (more on this below). </p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Google Analytics</p>
<p>Cheat Happens utilizes Google Analytics to gather information on our visitors and track certain site stats and metrics. IP anonymization is automatically enabled for all data collected by Google Analytics. </p>

