<p class="header16 openbold">Alexa Certified Metrics</p>
<p>Cheat Happens utilizes tracking code throughout the site in order to provide accurate metrics via Alexa.com. This code is included if you opted in to the "Statistics" section of our cookie declaration, however you may choose to opt in/out of this data collection separately if you choose.</p>
<p><a href="#" class="__alx_opt_out_class">Click here to opt out of Alexa Certified Site Metrics</a>.<br>
<a href="#" class="__alx_opt_in_class">Click here to opt in to Alexa Certified Site Metrics</a>. </p>
<p class="header16 openbold">LiveChat</p>
<p>Cheat Happens utilizes LiveChat (www.livechatinc.com) to provide members and guests with assistance through real-time chat and support tickets. Our LiveChat software is GDPR compliant and you can read their privacy policy here: <a href="https://www.livechatinc.com/privacy-policy/" target="_blank"><u>https://www.livechatinc.com/privacy-policy/</u></a>. You may request a transcript of chats and support tickets along with other personal information gathered by our LiveChat software by <a href="mailto:chusupport@cheathappens.com?subject=GDPR LiveChat Information Request"><u>clicking here</u></a>. If you would like for us to purge your chats and support tickets along with other personal information gathered by our LiveChat software, please <a href="mailto:chusupport@cheathappens.com?subject=GDPR LiveChat Purge Request"><u>click here</u></a>. Please note that depending on your response to our cookie declaration policy, you may not see or be able to use the LiveChat system.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">ProveSource</p>
<p>Information about the consent to ProveSource processing of personal data: We obtain your consent to the processing of personal data on the behalf of Configo LTD (“ProveSource”). Information collected from cookies set in your device that qualify as personal data will be processed by ProveSource, a company offering social proof marketing platform with offices in Israel. Please see below for full contact details. The purpose for the processing of the personal data is that it enables ProveSource to improve a service rendered to us and our website (e.g “Social Proof Notifications” service), by adding data to their database about leads, sales, and website visits.
The data that is collected and used by ProveSource to achieve this purpose is information about your session, and technical information that enables ProveSource to track your website activities. ProveSource stores your page visits and form input, excluding sensitive information like credit card details, passwords etc. You may at any time withdraw your consent to this processing. Such withdrawal may be made either by contacting us, or by contacting ProveSource directly:
