<p class="header16 openbold">Links</p>
<p>This web site contains links to other sites. Please be aware that Cheat Happens is not responsible for the privacy practices of such other sites. We encourage our users to be aware when they leave our site and to read the privacy statements of each and every web site that collects personally identifiable information. This privacy policy applies solely to information collected by this site.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Your Privacy Rights</p>
<p>Under the GDPR, you have a right to request all personally identifiable information that we collect and store on our server as well as the option to have this data purged at any time. This data is only stored for registered users and the option to request or purge this data can be found under the PRIVACY tab of the <a href="https://www.cheathappens.com/user_edit.asp">user account settings page</a>. You must be logged into your account to access these options. Optionally, you may open a <a href="https://www.cheathappens.com/support.asp">support ticket</a> to make these requests.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Email Options</p>
<p>Cheat Happens uses the email address of registered users in order to notify them of site updates, changes, notifications of updated content as well as password and security Q&A resets. Users may opt in or out of these emails through the PRIVACY tab of the <a href="https://www.cheathappens.com/user_edit.asp">user account settings page</a>. Note that some emails, specifically those related to site operation and important updates, will still be delivered even if you have opted out of receiving emails. Examples include lost password reset and updates to our privacy policies.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Notification of Changes</p>
<p>If changes or updates are made to our privacy policy, we will post those changes on our homepage so our users are always aware of what information we collect, how we use it, and under what circumstances, if any, we disclose it. If at any point we decide to use personally identifiable information in a manner different from that stated at the time it was collected, we will notify users on our homepage. Users will have a choice as to whether or not we use their information in this different manner. We will use information in accordance with the privacy policy under which the information was collected.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold"><u>CHEAT HAPPENS APPLICATIONS</u>:</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Cheat Happens Personalized Trainers</p>
<p>In an effort to maintain the integrity of the files downloaded from our site and to prevent
illegal file sharing, our personalized trainers will perform an authenticity check while in use. This check
requires an internet connection and the trainer will not run if a connection is absent or if the
trainer is blocked by a security application. The only information sent to Cheat Happens during this process is a uniquely generated string that can only be used to identify the member for which the trainer was personalized. This information is useless outside of the Cheat Happens website as it does not correlate to any personally identifiable information. As a part of routine website logging, the originating IP address may also be collected. This check is only performed on trainers that have been
personalized for individual use, not our PROMO or FREE trainers. If you want/need to use the
trainer offline, please go to our <a href="https://www.cheathappens.com/trainer_troubleshooting.asp">trainer troubleshooting page</a> for instructions on how to obtain
an offline key to avoid online checks. Some trainers may collect and show debug information which may contain some personally identifiable information in plain text. This information is not automatically sent to the Cheat Happens website. It is up to the end user to submit this information in order to help with troubleshooting trainer functionality. Some trainers may also feature a report function allowing users to send feedback to Cheat Happens. This feature may contain email address or other personally identifiable information but is optional. </p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Cheat Happens is a Software as a Service Company</p>
<p>Cheat Happens offers two different types of personalized software downloads, those that are purchased individually and those that are downloaded via a membership. Beginning on January 1, 2019, an active (non-expired) membership will be required for personalized trainers to continue to function. The only exceptions to this are those trainers that were purchased individually and/or those people that are eligible to download an offline key. Once a membership expires, all trainers will become disabled and will be unable to authenticate online until the membership is renewed or brought back to active status. Once that happens, previously banned trainers will work again. </p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Cheat Happens Offline Key Tool</p>
<p>This tool may be downloaded from our <a href="https://www.cheathappens.com/trainer_troubleshooting.asp">trainer troubleshooting page</a> in order to generate an offline key that can be used to authenticate personalized trainers in an offline situation. This tool collects hardware specific information about the user's computer which is then used to generate a unique string of characters that correlates to a Cheat Happens user account. No personally identifiable information is included in the data obtain or sent back to Cheat Happens by this tool.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Cheat Happens Trainer Manager</p>
<p>This tool consists of two parts. One is a built-in web browser in which everything listed above under "CHEAT HAPPENS WEBSITE" applies. The second part is a compilation of personalized trainers located on the user's computer. If selected by the user, the application can check for new versions of trainers as well as the trainer manager application by making a simple request to the Cheat Happens website containing only information about the trainer and/or application, not the user. As a part of routine website logging, the originating IP address may be collected.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold">Cheat Happens CoSMOS</p>
<p>This tool performs a routine check to see if a new version is available. No personal information is sent during this process. As a part of routine website logging, the originating IP address may be collected. A feedback as well as crash log routine is included in which users may choose to send this data to Cheat Happens. This may contain email address or other personally identifiable information but is optional.</p>
<p class="header16 openbold"><u>CHEAT HAPPENS COOKIE DECLARATION</u>:</p>
<strong>NOTE</strong>: If you are not seeing our cookie declaration then it means that your IP address has been identified as outside of the EU and does not require consent as a part of the GDPR. If you feel this is an error, please contact chris@cheathappens.com with your public IP address so that it can be investigated.<p>
